### Before reporting an issue

- [x] I have read and understood the above terms for submitting issues, and I understand that my issue may be closed without action if I do not follow them.

### Area

user-profile

### Describe the bug

In #34033 @ssilvert  and @edewit  helped me to get multiselect options working. This worked great until I finally found time to upgrade to the latest keycloak.

Stepping back I found that 26.4.0 is the first one, where I can't select anything anymore.

My RealmSettings:

<img width="959" height="722" alt="Image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/cde6c304-836d-469c-a60f-3531b15089ea" />

<img width="985" height="471" alt="Image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/df9a4bc9-edd8-449e-9eee-de333373e618" />


### Version

26.5.1

### Regression

- [x] The issue is a regression

### Expected behavior

Up until 26.3.5 I can create a user with this additional attribute and can choose one or multiple values.

### Actual behavior

Since 26.4.0 I can select items, but they never show up in the ui as selected nor get saved...

### How to Reproduce?

Start a new instance, edit the Realm settings -> User profile and Create attribute as shown above.

Then you can't select any value with the multiselect

